The Senior Quantity Surveyor is responsible for delivering comprehensive cost planning, tender
documentation, contract administration and commercial management services across
multidisciplinary design projects. The role ensures cost efficiency, commercial compliance, and
robust change management from concept design through project completion. The QS supports
project teams with accurate cost intelligence, tender evaluations, and contract oversight in
alignment with CPG’s standards and client requirements.

Key Responsibilities
• Estimate cost, build up manpower rate during pre-tender stage;
• Prepare cost plans, estimates, and Bills of Quantities (BoQ);
• Advise design teams on cost control, value engineering, and procurement strategies (if any);
• Prepare and review tender documents, evaluate tenders, and provide award recommendations;
• Administer contracts (FIDIC preferred), including variations, claims, and final accounts;
• Monitor project budgets, cash flow forecasts, and cost reports;
• Collect, analyze, and maintain up-to-date cost databases using government schedules, published indices, and market surveys to support reliable cost estimates and commercial decisions;
• Liaise with clients, consultants, and contracts on commercial terms;
• Ensure compliance with local regulations, client standards, and Company procedures;
• Mentor junior QS staff and support team development.

